import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['cx'], bins=10, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='cx')
    plt.axvline(data['cx'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['cx'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('cx')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cx?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['cy'], bins=10, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='cy')
    plt.axvline(data['cy'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['cy'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('cy')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cy?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['cx'], data['cy'], c=data.index, cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('cx')
    plt.ylabel('cy')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between cx and cy?', wrap=True)
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Boroughs")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='cx', ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(data['name'], data['cx'], color='c')
    ax.axhline(data['cx'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max cx: {data['cx'].max():.2f}")
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Location')
    plt.ylabel('cx Value')
    plt.title('Which location has the highest cx value?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
